p>"},"sn14.18:5.1":{"pli":"Dhātusova, bhikkhave …pe… ","eng":"Sentient beings come together because of an element: ","html":"<p data-counter='4'>{}"},"sn14.18:5.2":{"pli":"assaddhā assaddhehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the faithless … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.18:5.3":{"pli":"kusītā kusītehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"lazy … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.18:5.4":{"pli":"duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"witless. ","html":"{}"},"sn14.18:5.5":{"pli":"saddhā saddhehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the faithful … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.18:5.6":{"pli":"āraddhavīriyā āraddhavīriyehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti …pe…. ","eng":"energetic … wise. ","html":"{}</p>"},"sn14.18:6.1":{"pli":"Dhātusova, bhikkhave …pe… ","eng":"Sentient beings come together because of an element: ","html":"<p data-counter='5'>{}"},"sn14.18:6.2":{"pli":"assaddhā assaddhehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the faithless … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.18:6.3":{"pli":"muṭṭhassatino muṭṭhassatīhi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"unmindful … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.18:6.4":{"pli":"duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"witless. ","html":"{}"},"sn14.18:6.5":{"pli":"saddhā saddhehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the faithful … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.18:6.6":{"pli":"upaṭṭhitassatino upaṭṭhitassatīhi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samentī”ti …pe…. ","eng":"mindful … wise.” ","html":"{}</p>"},"sn14.18:6.7":{"pli":"Aṭṭhamaṁ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"sn14.19":{"sn14.19:0.1":{"pli":"Saṁyutta Nikāya 14.19 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 14.19 ","html":"<article id='sn14.19'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn14.19:0.2":{"pli":"2. Dutiyavagga ","eng":"Chapter Two ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn14.19:0.3":{"pli":"Ahirikamūlakasutta ","eng":"Beginning With the Shameless ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn14.19:1.1":{"pli":"Sāvatthiyaṁ viharati. ","eng":"At Sāvatthī. ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn14.19:1.2":{"pli":"“Dhātusova …pe… ","eng":"“Mendicants, sentient beings join together and converge because of an element: ","html":"<p data-counter='1'>{}"},"sn14.19:1.3":{"pli":"ahirikā ahirikehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, anottappino anottappīhi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; hirimanā hirimanehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, ottappino ottappīhi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti …pe…. ","eng":"the unconscientious with the unconscientious … imprudent … witless. The conscientious with the conscientious … prudent … wise. ","html":"{}</p>"},"sn14.19:2.1":{"pli":"Ahirikā ahirikehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, appassutā appassutehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; hirimanā hirimanehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, bahussutā bahussutehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti …pe…. ","eng":"… shameless … unlearned … witless. The conscientious with the conscientious … learned … wise. ","html":"<p data-counter='2'>{}</p>"},"sn14.19:3.1":{"pli":"Ahirikā ahirikehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, kusītā kusītehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; hirimanā hirimanehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, āraddhavīriyā āraddhavīriyehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti …pe…. ","eng":"… shameless … lazy … witless. The conscientious with the conscientious … energetic … wise. ","html":"<p data-counter='3'>{}</p>"},"sn14.19:4.1":{"pli":"Ahirikā ahirikehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, muṭṭhassatino muṭṭhassatīhi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; hirimanā hirimanehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, upaṭṭhitassatino upaṭṭhitassatīhi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti, paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samentī”ti …pe…. ","eng":"… shameless … unmindful … witless. The conscientious with the conscientious … mindful … wise.” ","html":"<p data-counter='4'>{}</p>"},"sn14.19:4.2":{"pli":"Navamaṁ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"sn14.2":{"sn14.2:0.1":{"pli":"Saṁyutta Nikāya 14.2 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 14.2 ","html":"<article id='sn14.2'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn14.2:0.2":{"pli":"1. Nānattavagga ","eng":"1. Diversity ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn14.2:0.3":{"pli":"Phassanānattasutta ","eng":"Diversity of Contacts ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn14.2:1.1":{"pli":"Sāvatthiyaṁ viharati. ","eng":"At Sāvatthī. ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn14.2:1.2":{"pli":"“Dhātunānattaṁ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṁ. ","eng":"“Mendicants, diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts. ","html":"<p>{}","comm":"The use of the word <i lang='pi' translate='no'>paṭicca</i> here connects back to dependent origination. Narrowing in on the particulars of sense experience, the text shows that particular factors give rise to other correlated factors, i.e. “this gives rise to this” (<a href='index.html?q=sn12.37#2.2'>SN 12.37:2.2</a>). "},"sn14.2:1.3":{"pli":"Katamañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṁ? ","eng":"And what is the diversity of elements? ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:1.4":{"pli":"Cakkhudhātu sotadhātu ghānadhātu jivhādhātu kāyadhātu manodhātu—","eng":"The eye element, ear element, nose element, tongue element, body element, and mind element. ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:1.5":{"pli":"idaṁ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṁ. ","eng":"This is called the diversity of elements. ","html":"{}</p>"},"sn14.2:2.1":{"pli":"Kathañca, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṁ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṁ? ","eng":"And how does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of contacts? ","html":"<p>{}"},"sn14.2:2.2":{"pli":"Cakkhudhātuṁ, bhikkhave, paṭicca uppajjati cakkhusamphasso. ","eng":"The eye element gives rise to eye contact. ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.3":{"pli":"Sotadhātuṁ paṭicca … ","eng":"The ear element … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.4":{"pli":"ghānadhātuṁ paṭicca … ","eng":"nose … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.5":{"pli":"jivhādhātuṁ paṭicca … ","eng":"tongue … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.6":{"pli":"kāyadhātuṁ paṭicca … ","eng":"body … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.7":{"pli":"manodhātuṁ paṭicca uppajjati manosamphasso. ","eng":"The mind element gives rise to mind contact. ","html":"{}"},"sn14.2:2.8":{"pli":"Evaṁ kho, bhikkhave, dhātunānattaṁ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattan”ti. ","eng":"That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts.” ","html":"{}</p>"},"sn14.2:2.9":{"pli":"Dutiyaṁ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"sn14.20":{"sn14.20:0.1":{"pli":"Saṁyutta Nikāya 14.20 ","eng":"Linked Discourses 14.20 ","html":"<article id='sn14.20'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"sn14.20:0.2":{"pli":"2. Dutiyavagga ","eng":"Chapter Two ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"sn14.20:0.3":{"pli":"Anottappamūlakasutta ","eng":"Beginning With Imprudence ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"sn14.20:1.1":{"pli":"Sāvatthiyaṁ viharati. ","eng":"At Sāvatthī. ","html":"<p>{}</p>"},"sn14.20:1.2":{"pli":"“Dhātusova, bhikkhave, sattā saṁsandanti samenti. ","eng":"“Mendicants, sentient beings join together and converge because of an element: ","html":"<p data-counter='1'>{}"},"sn14.20:1.3":{"pli":"Anottappino anottappīhi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"the imprudent with the imprudent … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.20:1.4":{"pli":"appassutā appassutehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"unlearned … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.20:1.5":{"pli":"duppaññā duppaññehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"witless. ","html":"{}"},"sn14.20:1.6":{"pli":"ottappino ottappīhi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; ","eng":"The prudent with the prudent … ","html":"{}"},"sn14.20:1.7":{"pli":"bahussutā bahussutehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti; paññavanto paññavantehi saddhiṁ saṁsandanti samenti …pe…. ","eng":"learned … wise. ","ht